1
00:00:10,720 --> 00:00:14,360
Having reached the end
of my sinner's life...

2
00:00:14,560 --> 00:00:16,680
my hair now white...

3
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:19,760
I prepare to leave
on this parchment my testimony...

4
00:00:19,840 --> 00:00:22,360
as to the wondrous
and terrible events...

5
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:24,640
I witnessed in my youth...

6
00:00:24,720 --> 00:00:29,920
at the end of the year of 1327.

7
00:00:30,440 --> 00:00:33,440
May God grant me
the wisdom and grace...

8
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:37,160
to be the faithful chronicler
of the happenings that took place...

9
00:00:37,280 --> 00:00:41,400
in a remote abbey
in the dark north of ltaly.

10
00:00:41,480 --> 00:00:45,760
An abbey whose name
it may seem, even now...

11
00:00:45,800 --> 00:00:48,920
bias andprudent to omit.

12
00:01:01,560 --> 00:01:06,360
THE NAME OF THE ROSE

13
00:03:15,240 --> 00:03:17,760
May my hand not tremble
now that I start...

14
00:03:17,840 --> 00:03:22,440
to relieve the past and
revive the feelings of uneasiness...

15
00:03:22,560 --> 00:03:26,520
that opressed my heart
as we entered the battlements.

16
00:04:00,920 --> 00:04:03,600
Should we tell him?

17
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:10,080
No. He will look
in the wrong places.

18
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:11,640
But...

19
00:04:12,480 --> 00:04:16,680
what if he learns it
of his own account?

20
00:04:16,880 --> 00:04:21,000
You're overestimating
his talents.

21
00:04:21,360 --> 00:04:25,560
There's only one authority
capable of investigating such matters.

22
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:29,800
The holly lnquisition.

23
00:04:35,680 --> 00:04:39,440
What's your opinion,
venerable Jorge?

24
00:04:41,480 --> 00:04:43,080
Dear brothers...

25
00:04:43,440 --> 00:04:48,320
I leave such worldly
matters to younger men.

26
00:05:02,120 --> 00:05:03,520
Adso?

27
00:05:04,360 --> 00:05:06,960
-Yes, master.
-To command nature...

28
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:10,400
one must learn
to obey it, huh?

29
00:05:10,720 --> 00:05:13,640
So, return to the court,
turn the building on your left...

30
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:17,560
enter the court on you right.
You'll find the place you're in need of...

31
00:05:17,680 --> 00:05:20,360
behind the third arch.

32
00:05:27,880 --> 00:05:31,040
But you told me you'd never
been to this abbey.

33
00:05:31,320 --> 00:05:34,960
When we arrived, I saw a
brother making this way so hazily.

34
00:05:35,320 --> 00:05:40,600
But he left more slowly,
with an air of content.

35
00:05:43,400 --> 00:05:45,800
Thank you, master.

36
00:06:24,680 --> 00:06:27,040
On behalf of the Benedict Order..

37
00:06:27,040 --> 00:06:30,720
I'm honored to welcome you
and your Franciscan brothers...

38
00:06:30,760 --> 00:06:33,520
to our abbey.

39
00:06:40,520 --> 00:06:44,320
The other delegates
have arrived?

40
00:06:44,360 --> 00:06:47,880
Ubertino de Casale has been
here for some weeks...

41
00:06:48,040 --> 00:06:51,000
the others are due tomorrow.

42
00:06:53,800 --> 00:06:58,160
You must be very tired
after your long journey.

43
00:06:58,480 --> 00:07:01,600
Not particularly.

44
00:07:03,480 --> 00:07:06,800
You're not in need
of anything?

45
00:07:06,960 --> 00:07:09,360
No, thank you.

46
00:07:09,560 --> 00:07:12,680
Well... then l...

47
00:07:13,960 --> 00:07:16,880
I beech you peace.

48
00:07:20,360 --> 00:07:22,680
I'm sorry to see that
one of your brothers...

49
00:07:22,800 --> 00:07:25,640
has recently gone
to God.

50
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:35,080
Yes, a terrible loss.

51
00:07:35,200 --> 00:07:38,440
Brother Adelmo was one
of our finest illuminates.

52
00:07:38,520 --> 00:07:40,840
-Not, Adelmo of Otranto?
-You knew him?

53
00:07:40,880 --> 00:07:43,840
No, but I knew and
admired his work.

54
00:07:43,920 --> 00:07:49,480
His humor and comic
images were almost infamous.

55
00:07:49,640 --> 00:07:51,040
But he was said to be very young.

56
00:07:51,160 --> 00:07:54,400
Ah, yes! Very young indeed.

57
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:56,960
An accident, no doubt.

58
00:07:57,040 --> 00:08:01,920
Yes, as you say, an accident.

59
00:08:03,440 --> 00:08:04,840
Well... that is l...

60
00:08:11,480 --> 00:08:13,800
Brother William...

61
00:08:14,520 --> 00:08:16,840
may I speak to you candidly?

62
00:08:16,960 --> 00:08:19,960
You seem anxious to do so.

63
00:08:20,080 --> 00:08:22,880
When I heard you were coming
to our abbey...

64
00:08:22,960 --> 00:08:26,480
I thought it was an answer
to my prayers.

65
00:08:26,600 --> 00:08:30,400
I said: "He's a man who has the
knowledge both of the human spirit...

66
00:08:30,440 --> 00:08:32,680
and of the wilds of the evil one."

67
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:36,400
Brother Adelmo's death
has caused much...

68
00:08:36,480 --> 00:08:40,480
spiritual
uneasy upon my flock.

69
00:08:42,440 --> 00:08:44,840
This is my novice, Adso.

70
00:08:44,960 --> 00:08:48,640
The youngest son of the
Baron de Melk.

71
00:08:49,560 --> 00:08:52,200
Please, do continue.

72
00:08:53,720 --> 00:08:56,480
We found the body
after a heavy storm...

73
00:08:56,560 --> 00:08:58,240
horribly mutilated...

74
00:08:58,600 --> 00:09:01,080
cast against a rock in
front of the tower...

75
00:09:01,160 --> 00:09:05,800
under a window that was...
How should I say this?

76
00:09:06,560 --> 00:09:09,240
-which was...
-which was found closed.

77
00:09:09,600 --> 00:09:12,880
-Somebody told you?
-lf it was opened...

78
00:09:12,920 --> 00:09:15,480
You'd not have mentioned
spiritual uneasy.

79
00:09:15,520 --> 00:09:18,200
-He'd have fallen.
-Brother William...

80
00:09:18,560 --> 00:09:21,760
the window can't be opened...

81
00:09:21,920 --> 00:09:24,200
nor was the glass shattered.

82
00:09:24,280 --> 00:09:28,200
There's no access
through the roof above.

83
00:09:28,520 --> 00:09:32,040
I see. As you can't
find a natural explanation...

84
00:09:32,160 --> 00:09:37,120
the monks suspect the
presence of supernatural forces.

85
00:09:37,440 --> 00:09:42,880
I need the help of an
acute man such as you.

86
00:09:43,160 --> 00:09:48,920
Acute in uncovering and
prudent, if necessary...

87
00:09:49,080 --> 00:09:54,600
in covering up before
the papal delegates arrive.

88
00:09:55,240 --> 00:09:58,720
You know I no longer deal
in such matters.

89
00:09:58,800 --> 00:10:03,560
I'm reluctant to burden
you with my dilemma, but...

90
00:10:04,840 --> 00:10:08,280
unless I can tranquilize
my flock...

91
00:10:08,600 --> 00:10:13,600
I have no alternative but
turn to the lnquisition.

92
00:10:47,520 --> 00:10:50,560
That is Ubertino de Casale...

93
00:10:50,680 --> 00:10:54,080
one of the greatest spiritual
leaders of our Order.

94
00:10:54,880 --> 00:10:56,520
Come.

95
00:11:08,720 --> 00:11:11,640
Many revere him
as a living saint...

96
00:11:11,760 --> 00:11:14,240
but others would have him
burnt as a heretic.

97
00:11:14,280 --> 00:11:16,080
His book on the poverty
of the clergy...

98
00:11:16,160 --> 00:11:18,600
isn't favorite
reading in the papal palace.

99
00:11:18,680 --> 00:11:21,240
So, now he lives
in hiding.

100
00:11:23,880 --> 00:11:27,080
Dear Franciscans...

101
00:11:27,160 --> 00:11:32,680
you must leave
this place at once.

102
00:11:32,760 --> 00:11:35,840
The devil's roaming this abbey!

103
00:11:35,960 --> 00:11:39,600
Ubertino, it's, William.

104
00:11:40,240 --> 00:11:42,760
Willian of Baskerville.

105
00:11:51,920 --> 00:11:56,080
William is dead.

106
00:12:03,560 --> 00:12:06,960
William... my son...

107
00:12:07,160 --> 00:12:09,120
forgive me.

108
00:12:09,320 --> 00:12:13,960
We lost trace ofyou
for so long!

109
00:12:14,040 --> 00:12:17,040
I tried hard to be forgotten.

110
00:12:17,120 --> 00:12:19,160
When we heard of your
troubles...

111
00:12:19,520 --> 00:12:23,040
I prayed to our Virgin
for a miracle.

112
00:12:23,120 --> 00:12:27,040
Your prayers met with a
favorable response.

113
00:12:27,240 --> 00:12:29,880
This is my young novice,
Adso de Melk.

114
00:12:29,960 --> 00:12:34,080
His father has entrusted
me his education and wealth.

115
00:12:37,560 --> 00:12:41,000
Let him out of here at once!
Haven't you heard the devil...

116
00:12:41,120 --> 00:12:45,800
is hurling beautiful
boys out of windows?

117
00:12:47,880 --> 00:12:52,760
There was something feminine...

118
00:12:53,760 --> 00:13:00,640
something diabolical...
about the young one who died.

119
00:13:01,080 --> 00:13:05,280
He had the eyes of a girl...

120
00:13:05,680 --> 00:13:10,200
seeking into course
with the devil.

121
00:13:11,320 --> 00:13:13,720
Beware of this place.

122
00:13:13,880 --> 00:13:17,840
The beast is still
among us.

123
00:13:17,920 --> 00:13:22,880
I can sense him...
now... here...

124
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:29,840
within these very walls.
I'm afraid, William.

125
00:13:30,040 --> 00:13:36,200
For you, for me.
For the outcome of this debate...

126
00:13:37,080 --> 00:13:43,280
My son!
The times we're living!

127
00:13:45,280 --> 00:13:52,240
Let's not frighten
our young friend.

128
00:13:55,840 --> 00:13:58,920
She's beautiful, isn't she?

129
00:14:01,200 --> 00:14:07,640
When a female...
by nature so perverted...

130
00:14:07,840 --> 00:14:11,640
becomes sublime by holiness...

131
00:14:11,760 --> 00:14:17,320
then she can be the
noble vehicle of grace.

132
00:14:18,240 --> 00:14:27,680
Beautiful are the breasts...
which feed only one baby.

133
00:14:35,680 --> 00:14:38,840
-I don't like this place.
-Really?

134
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:42,360
I find it thrillingly.
Come.

135
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:47,920
We must not allow ourselves
to be influenced...

136
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:51,080
by irrational rumors
of the antichrist.

137
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:54,160
Let's instead exercise
our brains...

138
00:14:54,280 --> 00:14:58,720
and try to solve this enigma.

139
00:14:58,880 --> 00:15:01,320
May you receive more in Heaven...

140
00:15:01,400 --> 00:15:05,320
for what you've given in Earth.

141
00:15:09,400 --> 00:15:12,720
My master trusted
Aristotle, the Greek philosopher...

142
00:15:12,760 --> 00:15:16,320
and in his remarkable
logic intelligence.

143
00:15:16,680 --> 00:15:18,760
Unhappily, my fears
were not...

144
00:15:18,880 --> 00:15:21,960
mere phantoms
of my youthful imagination.

145
00:15:22,680 --> 00:15:25,960
A rather dark end for such
a brilliant illuminate.

146
00:15:43,760 --> 00:15:47,040
Another generous donation
by the Church to the poor.

147
00:15:48,920 --> 00:15:52,080
What if it wasn't that tower
he fell from...

148
00:15:52,160 --> 00:15:57,360
but somewhere over there and
the body rolled all the way down here?

149
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:03,320
No devil needed anymore.

150
00:16:19,720 --> 00:16:22,040
There's more blood here.

151
00:16:23,040 --> 00:16:25,040
That's where he fell from.

152
00:16:25,240 --> 00:16:26,960
He jumped.

153
00:16:30,680 --> 00:16:33,680
-Are you paying attention?
-Yes, he jumped.

154
00:16:35,280 --> 00:16:38,800
Jumped? You mean that
he committed suicide?

155
00:16:38,840 --> 00:16:42,840
Why else would someone go up
there in the middle of a rainstorm?

156
00:16:43,120 --> 00:16:46,080
Not to admire the landscape.

157
00:16:46,240 --> 00:16:49,280
Perhaps someone murdered him.

158
00:16:49,760 --> 00:16:52,880
And then towed all the
way up there with the body?

159
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:57,120
Much easier to get rid of it
through that small door.

160
00:16:58,400 --> 00:17:02,480
My dear Adso.
It seems elementary.

161
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:08,080
Suicide?

162
00:17:08,240 --> 00:17:13,760
Do you think this is a place
abandoned by God?

163
00:17:13,840 --> 00:17:18,360
Have you ever known a place
where God would've felt at home?

164
00:17:21,720 --> 00:17:25,360
We pray, oh, mighty God,
that there are no grounds...

165
00:17:25,440 --> 00:17:29,800
for suspecting the presence
of an evil spirit among us...

166
00:17:29,920 --> 00:17:34,240
either of this world or another.

167
00:17:35,320 --> 00:17:38,280
We praise our Lord
that the debate...

168
00:17:38,360 --> 00:17:41,960
we are so greatly honored to host...

169
00:17:42,080 --> 00:17:47,160
may now proceed
without a shadow of fear.

170
00:17:49,160 --> 00:17:53,720
We also praise oh mighty
for sending us brother William...

171
00:17:53,920 --> 00:17:56,920
whose experience and
previous duties...

172
00:17:57,000 --> 00:18:03,400
although onerous to him...
has been of such service to us here.

173
00:18:03,960 --> 00:18:07,200
May serenity and
spiritual peace...

174
00:18:07,960 --> 00:18:12,920
reign once more
in our hearts.

175
00:18:30,280 --> 00:18:33,280
A monk must be quiet.

176
00:18:33,320 --> 00:18:38,440
He mustn't speak
what he's thinking...

177
00:18:38,520 --> 00:18:44,760
until he's asked.

178
00:18:46,520 --> 00:18:49,960
A monk mustn't laugh.

179
00:18:50,040 --> 00:18:56,120
That's what fools are for...

180
00:18:56,240 --> 00:19:00,920
who raise their voices in laughter.

181
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:22,960
Master, if I may ask what...

182
00:19:23,160 --> 00:19:28,120
onerous duties was
the abbot talking about?

183
00:19:28,360 --> 00:19:30,960
Were you not always a monk?

184
00:19:31,160 --> 00:19:34,400
Even monks have past, Adso.

185
00:19:35,560 --> 00:19:37,440
Now, try to sleep.

186
00:19:37,840 --> 00:19:39,240
Just...

187
00:19:41,040 --> 00:19:43,920
Yes, master.

188
00:19:48,120 --> 00:19:55,840
There's sadness in wisdom.

189
00:19:55,960 --> 00:19:58,840
The one who increases his knowledge...

190
00:19:58,920 --> 00:20:05,240
also increases his suffering.

191
00:22:28,400 --> 00:22:29,840
A calamity!

192
00:22:29,960 --> 00:22:32,880
It was a calamity!

193
00:22:34,360 --> 00:22:38,360
Father! A tragedy in the pigpen!

194
00:22:38,520 --> 00:22:42,480
Come! Come quickly!

195
00:23:02,640 --> 00:23:06,080
This one, I admit, didn't
commit suicide.

196
00:23:37,640 --> 00:23:38,920
Water!

197
00:23:43,640 --> 00:23:46,200
Venancius, the Greek translator!

198
00:23:51,240 --> 00:23:56,160
I'm to blame. Had I not been so eager
to believe your convenient explanation...

199
00:23:56,240 --> 00:23:58,200
this second tragedy
might've been prevented.

200
00:23:58,320 --> 00:24:02,400
I'm convinced brother Adelmo
took his own life.

201
00:24:05,920 --> 00:24:10,120
Whether this death is connected
with it. I intend to find.

202
00:24:10,200 --> 00:24:15,000
"After the heavy storm,
with the second trumpet..."

203
00:24:15,200 --> 00:24:19,600
"the sea became blood."

204
00:24:19,640 --> 00:24:27,200
-And hold... there's blood here!
-The prophecy of the Apocalypse.

205
00:24:27,360 --> 00:24:32,720
"With the third trumpet,
a burning star..."

206
00:24:32,960 --> 00:24:37,440
"will fall in fountains of water'

207
00:24:40,120 --> 00:24:42,920
The devil is here!

208
00:24:54,680 --> 00:24:58,080
Grated stem bistort
for treating diarrhea.

209
00:24:58,200 --> 00:25:02,040
As for onions, administered
in small quantities...

210
00:25:02,160 --> 00:25:06,520
warm and moist, they help to
prolong the male erection.

211
00:25:06,720 --> 00:25:09,960
In those who haven't taken
our vows, naturally.

212
00:25:22,440 --> 00:25:27,720
Do you apply arsenic in
many circumstances?

213
00:25:28,960 --> 00:25:30,200
Yes, indeed.

214
00:25:30,400 --> 00:25:33,560
This effective remedy for
nervous disorders.

215
00:25:34,360 --> 00:25:37,240
If taken in small doses.

216
00:25:37,560 --> 00:25:40,600
And what if not in so small doses?

217
00:25:42,320 --> 00:25:44,200
Death.

218
00:25:52,520 --> 00:25:55,200
What was his function here?

219
00:25:55,520 --> 00:25:58,520
He was our finest translator
of Greek.

220
00:25:58,640 --> 00:26:01,480
Entirely devoted to the works
of Aristotle.

221
00:26:01,560 --> 00:26:04,120
Was he in friendly terms with
the handsome Adelmo?

222
00:26:04,200 --> 00:26:07,680
Yes. They worked together in
the escritoire.

223
00:26:08,360 --> 00:26:11,680
But in a brotherly way
understand? Not like...

224
00:26:12,680 --> 00:26:16,680
I mean... flesh can be tempted
according to nature...

225
00:26:16,760 --> 00:26:19,440
or against nature.

226
00:26:19,520 --> 00:26:24,560
And they weren't allowed to
this position... you see!

227
00:27:26,240 --> 00:27:29,440
Penitengiazite!

228
00:27:31,480 --> 00:27:35,200
Watch out for Satan,
who comes to know your soul.

229
00:27:35,360 --> 00:27:38,480
Death is supreme.

230
00:27:43,400 --> 00:27:46,480
Contemplating my sanctuary?

231
00:27:46,720 --> 00:27:50,560
There, we have the devil.

232
00:27:55,080 --> 00:27:57,480
As ugly as Salvatore.

233
00:27:59,360 --> 00:28:03,160
My little brother,
penitenziagite.

234
00:28:03,840 --> 00:28:06,400
"Penitenziagite"?

235
00:28:11,240 --> 00:28:13,200
I didn't say that.

236
00:28:13,280 --> 00:28:15,840
You said "penitenziagite".
I heard.

237
00:28:18,200 --> 00:28:21,760
Noble father, "magnifico"!

238
00:28:22,440 --> 00:28:29,120
I don't have a good rhetoric.
I said "penitence".

239
00:28:29,200 --> 00:28:33,760
I'm a monk. Saint Benedict!
Saint Benedict!

240
00:28:34,400 --> 00:28:37,080
Salvatore, come here.

241
00:28:46,240 --> 00:28:50,480
Master, what language was
he speaking?

242
00:28:50,720 --> 00:28:54,520
All languages and none.

243
00:28:54,720 --> 00:28:58,480
And what was the word you
both repeated?

244
00:28:58,640 --> 00:29:01,320
"Penitenziagite"?

245
00:29:01,400 --> 00:29:05,240
-What does it mean?
-That the hunchback, undoubtedly...

246
00:29:05,280 --> 00:29:07,440
was once a herectic.

247
00:29:08,400 --> 00:29:12,360
"Penitenziagite" was the rally
cry of Dolcinites.

248
00:29:12,440 --> 00:29:15,440
Dolcinites? Who were they?

249
00:29:15,560 --> 00:29:18,400
Those who believed
in the poverty of Christ.

250
00:29:18,480 --> 00:29:20,480
So do we, Franciscans.

251
00:29:20,520 --> 00:29:23,120
But they also declared everyone
must be poor.

252
00:29:23,240 --> 00:29:25,280
So, they slaughtered the rich.

253
00:29:28,400 --> 00:29:30,320
You see, Adso...

254
00:29:30,480 --> 00:29:34,440
the step between ecstatic vision
and sinful frenzy...

255
00:29:34,520 --> 00:29:36,680
is all too brief.

256
00:29:37,880 --> 00:29:42,480
So, could he not have killed
the translator?

257
00:29:42,640 --> 00:29:45,760
No. Fat bishops and wealthy priests...

258
00:29:45,800 --> 00:29:48,560
were more to the taste
of the Dolcinites...

259
00:29:48,640 --> 00:29:51,720
not a specialist of Aristotle.

260
00:29:51,840 --> 00:29:55,120
But you're right, we must
keep the mind open.

261
00:30:01,360 --> 00:30:04,720
We're fortunate to have such
a snowy ground here.

262
00:30:04,800 --> 00:30:07,520
It's the parchment on which
the criminal, unwillingly...

263
00:30:07,640 --> 00:30:09,320
writes his autograph.

264
00:30:10,160 --> 00:30:12,920
What do you mean from these
footprints here?

265
00:30:13,360 --> 00:30:17,160
They're twice as deep as the
others, Master.

266
00:30:17,240 --> 00:30:19,840
Good! And thus we may conclude...

267
00:30:21,280 --> 00:30:22,760
That the man was very heavy.

268
00:30:22,840 --> 00:30:26,840
Precisely! And why was
he very heavy?

269
00:30:28,200 --> 00:30:31,480
Because... he was very fat?

270
00:30:31,560 --> 00:30:35,920
Or because he was carrying
another man.

271
00:30:38,160 --> 00:30:43,560
Let's commit the autograph
of this sole to our memory.

272
00:30:45,280 --> 00:30:49,440
But the footprints lead away
from the jar, in this direction.

273
00:30:50,480 --> 00:30:53,160
Adso, you're discounting
the possibility...

274
00:30:53,280 --> 00:30:56,600
that the man was walking
backwards, dragging the body...

275
00:30:57,240 --> 00:30:59,920
into the furrows
created by the heels.

276
00:31:01,240 --> 00:31:03,840
Where did the erudite
Greek translator...

277
00:31:04,120 --> 00:31:07,760
meet the anonymous
author of his death?

278
00:31:35,320 --> 00:31:37,480
Brother librarian...

279
00:31:37,680 --> 00:31:41,640
perhaps you'd permit us to examine
the work of the two unfortunates...

280
00:31:41,680 --> 00:31:44,600
who were so distressingly
gone to God.

281
00:31:44,760 --> 00:31:50,240
-Your request's most unusual.
-As are the circumstances of their deaths.

282
00:31:57,840 --> 00:32:00,160
Brother Adelmo sat there.

283
00:32:11,680 --> 00:32:14,240
Eyeglasses in frames.

284
00:32:23,440 --> 00:32:27,960
A donkey teaching the
Scriptures to the bishops.

285
00:32:30,280 --> 00:32:34,640
The pope as a fox.
And the abbot as a monkey.

286
00:32:36,640 --> 00:32:40,960
He had a daring talent
for comic images.

287
00:32:48,280 --> 00:32:52,760
A monk must not laugh!
Only fools laugh for nothing!

288
00:32:54,600 --> 00:32:57,840
I trust my words didn't
offend you brother William...

289
00:32:58,000 --> 00:33:02,240
but I heard them laughing
at unlaughable things.

290
00:33:02,320 --> 00:33:04,880
You, Franciscans, however,
belong to an Order...

291
00:33:05,000 --> 00:33:07,680
where merriment is viewed
with indulges.

292
00:33:07,760 --> 00:33:10,760
Yes, it's true. Saint Francis
was much disposed to laughter.

293
00:33:10,960 --> 00:33:16,280
Laughter's a devil's squint
which deforms the face...

294
00:33:16,360 --> 00:33:18,800
and makes men look
like monkeys.

295
00:33:18,880 --> 00:33:24,200
Monkeys do not laugh.
Laughter's particular to man.

296
00:33:24,320 --> 00:33:27,360
As a sin.
Christ never laughed.

297
00:33:27,440 --> 00:33:28,560
Can you be so sure?

298
00:33:28,680 --> 00:33:31,400
There's nothing in the
Scriptures to say that He did.

299
00:33:31,480 --> 00:33:33,880
There's nothing there
to say He didn't.

300
00:33:33,920 --> 00:33:36,640
Even the saints also
employed comedy...

301
00:33:36,720 --> 00:33:39,400
to ridicule the enemies
of the faith.

302
00:33:39,480 --> 00:33:42,520
For example, when the
pagans plunged Saint Maurus...

303
00:33:42,640 --> 00:33:43,960
into the boiling water,
he complained...

304
00:33:44,240 --> 00:33:47,440
that his bath was cold.
The Sultan put his hand in...

305
00:33:47,480 --> 00:33:50,240
-and burnt himself.
-A saint...

306
00:33:50,280 --> 00:33:54,640
immersed in boiling water
doesn't play childish tricks.

307
00:33:54,760 --> 00:33:59,360
He restrains his cries
and suffers for the truth.

308
00:33:59,520 --> 00:34:03,960
And yet, Aristotle devoted his second
book of poetics to comedy...

309
00:34:04,240 --> 00:34:07,560
as an instrument of truth.

310
00:34:08,680 --> 00:34:10,040
Have you read this work?

311
00:34:10,280 --> 00:34:12,680
Of course not.
It's been lost for centuries.

312
00:34:12,760 --> 00:34:15,640
No, it's not!
It was never written!

313
00:34:15,720 --> 00:34:19,960
Because Providence doesn't
want futile things glorified.

314
00:34:20,240 --> 00:34:22,560
-That I must contempt.
-Enough!

315
00:34:22,640 --> 00:34:25,960
This abbey is overshadowed by grief.
Yet you would...

316
00:34:26,000 --> 00:34:30,400
intrude on our sorrows
with idle banter!

317
00:34:31,840 --> 00:34:36,840
Forgive me, Venerable Jorge.
My remarks were truly out of place.

318
00:34:41,760 --> 00:34:44,440
Which was the Greek
translator's desk?

319
00:34:44,840 --> 00:34:46,600
This one.

320
00:34:58,560 --> 00:34:59,960
Come, Adso.

321
00:35:10,560 --> 00:35:16,800
-What'd you deduce from that visit?
-That we're not meant to laugh in there.

322
00:35:17,000 --> 00:35:21,560
But you noticed how few books
there were on the escritoire's shelves?

323
00:35:22,000 --> 00:35:26,000
All those scriveners, copyists,
translators, researchers...

324
00:35:26,280 --> 00:35:30,240
thinkers... Where are the books
needed for their work...

325
00:35:30,360 --> 00:35:34,440
and for which this abbey
is famous?

326
00:35:34,520 --> 00:35:37,680
Where are the books?

327
00:35:38,960 --> 00:35:42,920
-Are you testing me?
-What do you mean?

328
00:35:43,400 --> 00:35:45,400
With all due respect...

329
00:35:45,520 --> 00:35:50,480
it seems that whenever you ask me a
question, you already have the answer.

330
00:35:51,360 --> 00:35:53,400
Do you know where the books are?

331
00:35:53,600 --> 00:36:01,600
No, but I've faith that that
tower contains something other than air.

332
00:36:10,600 --> 00:36:15,400
Did you see the little door
the librarian closed as we came in?

333
00:36:15,600 --> 00:36:17,080
That leads to the library?

334
00:36:33,720 --> 00:36:37,080
Master! Quick! I have him!

335
00:36:38,480 --> 00:36:42,840
-Stop! Enough.
-He tried to kill us.

336
00:36:46,600 --> 00:36:47,640
Salvatore!

337
00:36:51,560 --> 00:36:56,320
Please, don't talk to the abbot
about his past.

338
00:36:56,480 --> 00:37:00,800
He's innocent of the deaths
in this abbey. I swear it.

339
00:37:02,640 --> 00:37:07,720
Brother Remigio, my price is
some information.

340
00:37:15,120 --> 00:37:18,720
I couldn't comprehend
why my master so quickly dismissed...

341
00:37:18,840 --> 00:37:21,840
my suspicions for the
heretic hunchback...

342
00:37:22,000 --> 00:37:25,040
and why it was so urgent
that we visited the tower.

343
00:37:25,560 --> 00:37:27,880
I assumed he couldn't
resist the temptation...

344
00:37:27,960 --> 00:37:31,920
to penetrate the library
and look at the books.

345
00:38:45,680 --> 00:38:49,600
No lock. Just as I thought,
it must be bolted from inside.

346
00:38:49,800 --> 00:38:51,400
How do we get in?

347
00:38:51,560 --> 00:38:53,800
Obviously, there must be
another entrance.

348
00:38:55,720 --> 00:38:58,200
Let's see what the moon-faced
assistant librarian...

349
00:38:58,480 --> 00:39:01,520
was trying to conceal this morning.

350
00:39:20,080 --> 00:39:22,040
Tiny Greek letters.

351
00:39:22,160 --> 00:39:25,960
Perhaps written by an ant
with ink feet.

352
00:39:26,160 --> 00:39:30,600
"Have fun with the defects
of vulgar people."

353
00:39:56,200 --> 00:39:58,880
Written with lemon juice.

354
00:40:05,480 --> 00:40:10,000
Sagittarius... Sun... Mercury...

355
00:40:11,160 --> 00:40:12,800
Scorpion.

356
00:40:14,800 --> 00:40:18,680
It's a zodiac code...
giving directions...

357
00:40:18,760 --> 00:40:20,960
but to where?

358
00:40:22,600 --> 00:40:25,480
Who's there?
Who's there?

359
00:40:45,680 --> 00:40:48,560
-My magnifying glasses...
-They were in that book.

360
00:40:55,520 --> 00:40:57,880
You go that way.

361
00:41:59,960 --> 00:42:03,040
Come on out, you little bitch!

362
00:42:03,920 --> 00:42:08,280
I know you're here.
I can smell you.

363
00:42:12,880 --> 00:42:17,720
What's the matter with you?
Are you afraid of me?

364
00:42:36,000 --> 00:42:38,000
I'll find you.

365
00:43:34,200 --> 00:43:35,960
Who was she?

366
00:43:36,120 --> 00:43:39,720
Who was this creature
that rose like the dawn...

367
00:43:39,880 --> 00:43:44,200
bewitched as the moon,
radiant as the sun..

368
00:43:44,520 --> 00:43:48,600
terrible as an army
poised for battle?

369
00:47:03,320 --> 00:47:05,280
Good evening, Salvatore.

370
00:47:11,080 --> 00:47:13,400
This is where you catch them?

371
00:47:15,800 --> 00:47:19,400
Here they're "piu grassi",
bigger.

372
00:47:19,880 --> 00:47:23,000
Do you eat them?

373
00:47:24,680 --> 00:47:28,440
-Do you like?
-Thank you, no.

374
00:47:28,760 --> 00:47:31,240
"lch bin" good catholic.

375
00:47:32,280 --> 00:47:36,120
As you're a good Christian,
you must tell me.

376
00:47:45,040 --> 00:47:49,320
So Adelmo gave the
parchment to Berengar?

377
00:47:49,400 --> 00:47:54,160
No. To the trans... tran...

378
00:47:54,240 --> 00:47:57,000
Translator! Venancius,
the black monk.

379
00:47:57,080 --> 00:47:58,840
What happened then?

380
00:48:32,720 --> 00:48:36,280
Master! Here, quick!
I found another one.

381
00:48:44,440 --> 00:48:47,160
Where are your wits, boy?

382
00:48:47,280 --> 00:48:50,080
Have you ever met anyone with a
rib cage large enough to accommodate...

383
00:48:50,120 --> 00:48:53,760
a heart of those dimensions?

384
00:48:58,000 --> 00:49:00,960
This is the heart of an ox.

385
00:49:01,800 --> 00:49:04,360
One of the monks probably
gave it to that peasant girl...

386
00:49:04,400 --> 00:49:07,760
in exchange for her favors.

387
00:49:08,120 --> 00:49:10,160
A girl? What?

388
00:49:11,280 --> 00:49:14,360
The one I saw out of here.

389
00:49:16,440 --> 00:49:20,520
-He must've been a very ugly monk.
-Why ugly?

390
00:49:23,960 --> 00:49:28,320
If he'd been young and beautiful,
she'd have blessed him...

391
00:49:28,360 --> 00:49:32,480
with her carnal favors for nothing.

392
00:49:32,760 --> 00:49:36,160
Whatever happened in this
dreadful kitchen...

393
00:49:36,360 --> 00:49:39,960
has no bearing on
our investigations.

394
00:49:40,160 --> 00:49:42,320
The hunchback's convinced
me that brother Berengar...

395
00:49:42,400 --> 00:49:45,400
the assistant librarian,
is the key to the whole enigma.

396
00:49:45,440 --> 00:49:49,840
-What did you say?
-Nothing, master.

397
00:49:50,000 --> 00:49:51,360
Good.

398
00:50:06,920 --> 00:50:08,280
Master?

399
00:50:11,560 --> 00:50:14,400
There's something I must tell you.

400
00:50:15,520 --> 00:50:17,520
I know.

401
00:50:19,760 --> 00:50:22,200
Then, you'll hear my confession?

402
00:50:22,280 --> 00:50:27,440
I'd rather you told me
first as a friend.

403
00:50:33,560 --> 00:50:34,880
Master...

404
00:50:36,760 --> 00:50:38,520
Have you ever been...

405
00:50:39,120 --> 00:50:43,360
in love?

406
00:50:43,840 --> 00:50:45,160
In love?

407
00:50:46,160 --> 00:50:49,000
-Many times.
-You were?

408
00:50:49,040 --> 00:50:52,960
Of course. Aristotle, Ovid,
Virgil...

409
00:50:53,040 --> 00:50:55,800
No. I meant with a...

410
00:50:57,560 --> 00:51:01,440
Are you not confusing love
with lust?

411
00:51:02,560 --> 00:51:04,160
Am l?

412
00:51:05,480 --> 00:51:07,040
I don't know.

413
00:51:08,440 --> 00:51:11,400
I want to make her own good.

414
00:51:12,840 --> 00:51:18,040
I want her to be happy.
I want to save her from poverty.

415
00:51:19,880 --> 00:51:21,240
Oh, dear!

416
00:51:21,560 --> 00:51:25,840
-Why "oh, dear"?
-You are in love.

417
00:51:26,000 --> 00:51:28,200
Is that bad?

418
00:51:29,040 --> 00:51:32,840
For a monk it presents
certain problems.

419
00:51:33,000 --> 00:51:36,440
But doesn't St Thomas Aquinas
praise love above all the virtues?

420
00:51:36,560 --> 00:51:41,040
Yes, the love of God, Adso.
Love of God!

421
00:51:45,920 --> 00:51:48,560
And the love of... woman?

422
00:51:48,960 --> 00:51:53,480
Of woman, Thomas Aquinas
knew very little.

423
00:51:53,560 --> 00:51:57,920
The Scriptures are very clear.
Proverbs warns us.

424
00:51:58,000 --> 00:52:00,600
Woman takes possession of a
man's precious soul.

425
00:52:00,880 --> 00:52:03,120
Ecclesiastes tells us:

426
00:52:03,600 --> 00:52:07,560
"More bitter than death is woman."

427
00:52:08,240 --> 00:52:12,040
Yes, but what do you think, master?

428
00:52:12,240 --> 00:52:17,440
Of course, I don't have the benefit
of your experience...

429
00:52:17,520 --> 00:52:23,360
but I find it difficult
to convince myself that...

430
00:52:24,320 --> 00:52:27,560
God'd have introduced such
a being into creation...

431
00:52:27,920 --> 00:52:31,520
without endowing her
with some virtues.

432
00:52:36,400 --> 00:52:40,560
How peaceful life'd be
without love, Adso.

433
00:52:41,240 --> 00:52:45,080
How safe... how tranquil...

434
00:52:48,040 --> 00:52:49,440
and how dull.

435
00:53:03,000 --> 00:53:07,560
God, You've guided us to
this refuge...

436
00:53:07,920 --> 00:53:11,560
of spiritual peace because
you wish for reconciliation...

437
00:53:11,960 --> 00:53:14,160
as much as we, Franciscans.

438
00:53:14,360 --> 00:53:16,360
Let's go, brothers!

439
00:53:21,840 --> 00:53:23,840
Brother Berengar?

440
00:53:30,360 --> 00:53:33,680
He's probably hiding
somewhere...

441
00:53:34,000 --> 00:53:37,480
with the book and
my magnifying glasses.

442
00:53:45,520 --> 00:53:47,520
Brother Berengar?

443
00:53:52,600 --> 00:53:55,560
Master, look! The door!

444
00:54:03,480 --> 00:54:05,960
Brother Malaquias!

445
00:54:06,040 --> 00:54:10,000
I was looking for brother Berengar.
Is he here?

446
00:54:10,200 --> 00:54:11,160
No.

447
00:54:12,240 --> 00:54:17,120
I see. Do you know where
we might find him?

448
00:54:17,960 --> 00:54:18,880
No.

449
00:54:18,960 --> 00:54:22,360
Or is he perhaps upstairs,
in the library?

450
00:54:22,440 --> 00:54:23,400
No.

451
00:54:24,480 --> 00:54:27,600
I'm curious to see the library
for myself. May I do so?

452
00:54:27,680 --> 00:54:28,680
No.

453
00:54:30,520 --> 00:54:31,880
Why not?

454
00:54:32,040 --> 00:54:34,400
It's strict order of the abbot.

455
00:54:34,560 --> 00:54:37,120
No one's permitted
to enter the library...

456
00:54:37,280 --> 00:54:40,200
other than myself and my assistant.

457
00:54:40,360 --> 00:54:44,520
I see. Thank you again.

458
00:54:56,600 --> 00:55:00,400
Maybe something's happened to him.

459
00:55:00,720 --> 00:55:03,160
Maybe we'll find him in the water.

460
00:55:03,240 --> 00:55:05,560
-What?
-The third trumpet...

461
00:55:05,640 --> 00:55:09,560
as Ubertino said.
The book of Revelation.

462
00:55:10,160 --> 00:55:13,320
That's not the book we're after.

463
00:55:20,480 --> 00:55:24,600
Is it a chicken for you?
It's more like a sparrow.

464
00:55:36,600 --> 00:55:38,040
Franciscans.

465
00:55:38,200 --> 00:55:41,520
Welcome to our abbey,
brother Michele.

466
00:55:41,680 --> 00:55:44,520
And your fellow Franciscan
delegates.

467
00:55:46,320 --> 00:55:48,440
Get in the line like the others!

468
00:55:49,480 --> 00:55:51,440
Salvatore, let him go!

469
00:55:51,600 --> 00:55:53,160
This is Cuthbert of Winchester...

470
00:55:53,240 --> 00:55:56,080
one of our most esteemed
Franciscan guests.

471
00:55:56,520 --> 00:56:00,720
Come, your grace. We have a
very urgent matter to discuss.

472
00:56:02,200 --> 00:56:04,600
The abbot and his colleagues
believe...

473
00:56:04,720 --> 00:56:07,280
the devil's at work
within these walls.

474
00:56:07,360 --> 00:56:09,640
He is!

475
00:56:10,000 --> 00:56:12,560
The only evidence I see
of the devil...

476
00:56:13,120 --> 00:56:15,520
is everyone's desire to see
him at work.

477
00:56:15,600 --> 00:56:18,000
What if Ubertino's right and
you're wrong?

478
00:56:18,120 --> 00:56:20,560
This debate's
crucial to us all.

479
00:56:20,640 --> 00:56:23,120
we suspect the Pope
wants to crash our Order.

480
00:56:23,240 --> 00:56:26,360
-And declare us heretics.
-Yes, and declare us heretics.

481
00:56:26,440 --> 00:56:32,040
I only have one brother to
question and the matter's resolved.

482
00:56:32,520 --> 00:56:36,160
William, we place our trust
in you.

483
00:56:36,240 --> 00:56:39,520
I pray God that you don't
abuse it.

484
00:56:43,720 --> 00:56:45,440
Brother William.

485
00:57:26,240 --> 00:57:28,560
Did you find a book in Greek?

486
00:57:42,720 --> 00:57:45,120
I was right.

487
00:57:45,200 --> 00:57:48,280
So was the book of
Revelation.

488
00:57:49,440 --> 00:57:53,440
-We must talk at once.
-lndeed, we must.

489
00:57:53,600 --> 00:57:55,800
And I have much to tell.

490
00:57:56,160 --> 00:58:00,480
Just as he and I've
examined this corpse.

491
00:58:03,040 --> 00:58:06,480
Lime leaves in the bath
are used to alleviate pain.

492
00:58:06,640 --> 00:58:08,680
He was left-handed?

493
00:58:08,760 --> 00:58:12,200
Brother Berengar was
inverted in many ways.

494
00:58:12,400 --> 00:58:15,600
Are there other left-handed
brothers at the abbey?

495
00:58:16,280 --> 00:58:17,440
Not that I know.

496
00:58:18,800 --> 00:58:20,560
Ink stains.

497
00:58:29,800 --> 00:58:32,760
He didn't write with his
tongue, I presume.

498
00:58:41,520 --> 00:58:47,440
-A few lines in Greek.
-Yes, written by Venancius.

499
00:58:47,560 --> 00:58:50,600
Notes from the book he
was reading...

500
00:58:50,680 --> 00:58:55,440
just before he died.
You see how the calligraphy changes?

501
00:58:57,320 --> 00:59:02,280
From this point on, he was dying.
And what can we conclude from that?

502
00:59:03,840 --> 00:59:07,360
A spot of blue paint.

503
00:59:07,560 --> 00:59:10,520
yes, but a unique spot
of blue...

504
00:59:10,640 --> 00:59:13,400
blended by your finest
illuminate, brother Adelmo...

505
00:59:13,520 --> 00:59:16,240
who had this parchment
before Venancius.

506
