996
01:48:59,200 --> 01:49:03,080
"We'll now discuss how comedy
stimulates the liking ridicule..."

997
01:49:03,240 --> 01:49:06,200
"by using vulgar persons..."

998
01:49:06,240 --> 01:49:08,920
"and taking pleasure from
their defects."

999
01:49:10,640 --> 01:49:15,560
-Carry on, William. Read it!
-Master, we must hurry.

1000
01:49:15,680 --> 01:49:17,680
If the light is too deem
for you, give it to the boy...

1001
01:49:18,280 --> 01:49:20,560
I'm sure he can read it.

1002
01:49:20,840 --> 01:49:25,920
I don't want my pupil
to turn your poisoned pages...

1003
01:49:26,160 --> 01:49:30,640
not without the protection
of a glove, such as I'm wearing.

1004
01:49:35,800 --> 01:49:38,400
The door! Quick,
before it closes!

1005
01:50:17,240 --> 01:50:21,800
Venerable brother, there are many
books that speak of comedy.

1006
01:50:21,840 --> 01:50:24,760
Why does this one
fill you with such fear?

1007
01:50:24,800 --> 01:50:27,520
Because it's by Aristotle.

1008
01:50:27,840 --> 01:50:28,640
This way.

1009
01:50:53,680 --> 01:50:57,600
Do you, Salvatore, renounce
the devil and embrace Jesus Christ...

1010
01:50:57,760 --> 01:51:00,920
as your Lord and Savior?

1011
01:51:08,760 --> 01:51:11,640
Do you, Remigio de Veragine,
renounce the devil...

1012
01:51:12,000 --> 01:51:13,640
-and embrace Jesus...
-What for?

1013
01:51:13,720 --> 01:51:16,480
It's better die fast
than to spend...

1014
01:51:16,520 --> 01:51:18,640
the rest of life in prison.

1015
01:51:18,680 --> 01:51:23,720
The devil I renounce
is you, Bernardo Gui.

1016
01:51:28,000 --> 01:51:32,560
Do you renounce the devil
and embrace Jesus as your Savior?

1017
01:51:37,520 --> 01:51:41,000
But what's so alarming
about laughter?

1018
01:51:41,360 --> 01:51:43,360
Laughter kills fear...

1019
01:51:43,440 --> 01:51:46,920
and without fear
there can't be faith.

1020
01:51:47,000 --> 01:51:49,000
And without fear to the devil...

1021
01:51:49,280 --> 01:51:52,960
there's no more need to God.

1022
01:51:53,560 --> 01:51:58,360
But you won't eliminate laughter
by eliminating that book.

1023
01:51:58,520 --> 01:52:00,640
No, to be sure.

1024
01:52:00,720 --> 01:52:04,280
Laughter will remain
the common man's recreation...

1025
01:52:04,360 --> 01:52:07,880
but what'll happen if,
because of this book...

1026
01:52:07,960 --> 01:52:11,640
Iearned men work
to pronounce permissible...

1027
01:52:11,800 --> 01:52:16,080
to laugh of everything?
Can we laugh at God?

1028
01:52:16,280 --> 01:52:19,720
The world would
be back to chaos.

1029
01:52:20,000 --> 01:52:25,480
Therefore, I seal that
which is not to be said...

1030
01:52:26,560 --> 01:52:30,320
in the tomb I become.

1031
01:52:33,880 --> 01:52:36,520
He's there, behind the arch!

1032
01:54:20,520 --> 01:54:22,840
Save me!

1033
01:54:26,560 --> 01:54:27,480
Look!

1034
01:54:51,160 --> 01:54:57,400
Courage, brother!
Remember Dolcino!

1035
01:55:12,080 --> 01:55:15,520
Go out! I insist!

1036
01:55:19,480 --> 01:55:23,360
Go out! I insist!.

1037
01:55:25,840 --> 01:55:28,080
God, save him.

1038
01:55:39,600 --> 01:55:40,840
Stay back.

1039
01:55:41,640 --> 01:55:44,000
Burn the witch!

1040
01:55:49,960 --> 01:55:52,920
Do you dare to raise your
hands to the Church?

1041
01:57:09,600 --> 01:57:10,840
You won't leave!

1042
01:57:11,000 --> 01:57:15,680
It's all your wrong doing!
My master found out the murderer!

1043
01:57:44,040 --> 01:57:45,200
Help me!

1044
01:58:30,800 --> 01:58:32,760
Master...

1045
02:01:35,640 --> 02:01:38,360
I never regretted
my decision...

1046
02:01:38,680 --> 02:01:42,160
for I learned from my master
what's wise...

1047
02:01:42,280 --> 02:01:44,840
and good and true.

1048
02:01:45,040 --> 02:01:48,920
When at last we parted,
he presented me with his glasses.

1049
02:01:49,080 --> 02:01:50,920
I was too young, he said...

1050
02:01:51,080 --> 02:01:53,240
but one day they'd
serve me well.

1051
02:01:53,440 --> 02:01:58,920
In fact, I'm wearing them now
while I write these lines.

1052
02:01:59,080 --> 02:02:04,400
He embraced me like a father...
and sent me on my way.

1053
02:02:04,760 --> 02:02:08,120
I never saw him again, and knew
nothing of what have become of him...

1054
02:02:08,280 --> 02:02:11,040
but I always prayed that God
received his soul...

1055
02:02:11,240 --> 02:02:14,200
and forgave his little
vanities to which was driven...

1056
02:02:14,320 --> 02:02:17,240
by his intellectual pride.

1057
02:02:17,480 --> 02:02:22,200
And yet, now that I'm
an old, old man...

1058
02:02:22,320 --> 02:02:27,000
I must confess that all the
faces that appeared to me out of the past...

1059
02:02:27,160 --> 02:02:30,920
the one I see most clearly
is that of the girl...

1060
02:02:31,160 --> 02:02:33,680
whom I never ceased
to dream...

1061
02:02:33,680 --> 02:02:36,960
these many long years.

1062
02:02:37,200 --> 02:02:41,160
She was the only earthly
love in my life...

1063
02:02:41,360 --> 02:02:46,280
yet I never knew
not ever learned...

1064
02:02:46,400 --> 02:02:47,920
her name.

1065
02:02:48,280 --> 02:02:54,000
Keep the name first of the rose,
without which we won't exist.

